---
// src/pages/_site-updates/2026-07-22-provider-trust-language.astro
export const updateMeta = {
  date: '2026-07-22',
  title: 'Provider pages: align "verified" copy with the no-verify/vet/vouch trust posture',
  tags: ['marketplace', 'providers', 'trust'],
};
---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">July 22, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
    Reworded provider-page copy that used &ldquo;Verified&rdquo; / &ldquo;Verification&rdquo; in a way
    that implied BreederHQ vets or vouches for providers. BreederHQ does not verify, vet, evaluate, or
    vouch — it surfaces facts (identity confirmation via Stripe Identity, public-registry passthrough,
    and provider self-attestation). Copy now matches the <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a> policy and the in-app product.
  </p>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-500 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
    <li><a href="/for-providers/equine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/equine-services</a> — the &ldquo;Verification&rdquo; section became &ldquo;Trust Signals&rdquo; (identity confirmation, self-attested insurance/memberships, registry passthrough, client reviews); removed &ldquo;Verified-provider badge&rdquo; and &ldquo;Verified Client Reviews.&rdquo;</li>
    <li><a href="/for-providers/farriers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/farriers</a> — credential FAQs reframed from &ldquo;we review and issue a verified credential badge&rdquo; to registry-passthrough / provider-attestation.</li>
    <li><a href="/for-providers/equine" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/equine</a> and <a href="/for-providers/dog-parks" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/dog-parks</a> — &ldquo;verified reviews&rdquo; / &ldquo;verification&rdquo; trust-panel wording softened to reviews / identity confirmation.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">
    Left as-is: legitimate uses of the word (Stripe Identity&rsquo;s own &ldquo;identity verification,&rdquo;
    DHIA milk-test &ldquo;verification&rdquo; plan names, genetics/health-test &ldquo;verification&rdquo; services).
  </p>
</article>
